
[1]portion

   PORTION, n. [L. portio, from partio, to divide, from pars, part. See
   Part.]

   1. In general, a part of any thing separated from it. Hence,

   2. A part, though not actually divided, but considered by itself.

   These are parts of his ways, but how little a portion is heard of him.
   Job.26.

   3. A part assigned; an allotment; a dividend.

   How small

   A portion to your share would fall.

   The priests had a portion assigned them of Pharaoh. Gen.47.

   4. The part of an estate given to a child or heir, or descending to him
   by law, and distributed to him in the settlement of the estate.

   5. A wife's fortune.

       PORTION, v.t. To divide; to parcel; to allot a share or shares.

   And portion to his tribes the wide domain.

   1. To endow.

   Him portion'd maids, apprentic'd orphans blest.
